name: ELEFANCLUB 06
description:
An original illustration for 50 randomly selected collectors (1+) of Les Elefants Terribles.

“A framed film tableaux,
beneath the twilight cathedral of moths.

A good luck and great fortune, 
brought from a landscape of rocks.

A struggle for breath,
in Esther Lucas’ roman à clef.

A jumpologist saving a duck,
with twenty-six airborne shots of luck.

A tap tap tap at the window pain,
it’s only bloody gee gee again.

A coronation drag banned by MTV,
screams Pope Francis’ the innocent XTZ.”

Rotring pen and markers on paper

By Guillaume Cornet and Only Child No Pets
Follow @elefants_tez on twitter
